<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code casts a const-qualified object (tiny_body, a const char * / string literal) to void * when calling MHD_create_response_from_buffer: (void *) tiny_body. This discards the const qualification and therefore uses a non-const pointer to refer to const data, violating the requirement that pointers should point to const-qualified types when possible.
</scenario>

